in studies conducted after 2011. Females are an underrepresented group in 
studies assessing the cardiovascular outcomes related to high-dose exercise. As 
cardiovascular outcomes vary between sexes, translating findings from a largely 
male-based evidence may not be appropriate. Future investigators should aim to 
establish and overcome barriers to female recruitment.

