Antioxidant Films from Cassava Starch/Gelatin Biocomposite Fortified with 
Quercetin and TBHQ and Their Applications in Food Models.

Tongdeesoontorn W(1)(2), Mauer LJ(3), Wongruong S(4), Sriburi P(5), Reungsang 
A(6)(7)(8), Rachtanapun P(9)(10)(11).

Author information:
(1)School of Agro-Industry, Mae Fah Luang University, Chiang Rai 57100, 
Thailand.
(2)Research Group of Innovative Food Packaging and Biomaterials Unit, Mae Fah 
Luang University, Chiang Rai 57100, Thailand.
(3)Department of Food Science, Purdue University, West Lafayette, IN 47907, USA.
(4)Division of Biotechnology, Faculty of Agro-Industry, Chiang Mai University, 
Chiang Mai 50100, Thailand.
(5)Department of Chemistry, Faculty of Science, Chiang Mai University, Chiang 
Mai 50200, Thailand.
(6)Department of Biotechnology, Faculty of Technology, Khon Kaen University, 
Khon Kaen 40002, Thailand.
(7)Research Group for Development of Microbial Hydrogen Production Process, Khon 
Kaen University, Khon Kaen 40002, Thailand.
(8)Academy of Science, Royal Society of Thailand, Bangkok 10300, Thailand.
(9)Division of Packaging Technology, Faculty of Agro-Industry, School of 
