The treatment and management of patients with metastatic melanoma have evolved 
considerably in the "era" of personalized medicine. Melanoma was one of the 
first solid tumors to benefit from immunotherapy; life expectancy for patients 
in advanced stage of disease has improved. However, many progresses have yet to 
be made considering the (still) high number of patients who do not respond to 
therapies or who suffer adverse events. In this scenario, precision medicine 
appears fundamental to direct the most appropriate treatment to the single 
patient and to guide towards treatment decisions. The recent multi-omics 
analyses (genomics, transcriptomics, proteomics, metabolomics, radiomics, etc.) 
